There's free COVID-19 testing happening this Friday (08/28) and Saturday (08/29)!

If you need to be tested, you can head to the Africentric Center (3223 Allegheny Ave., 43209). Hours are 10 a.m. - 7 p.m. on Friday and 8 a.m. - 8 p.m. on Saturday.

These testing events are open to the public and available to anyone in the community (adults and children), but strictly for those who are uninsured or on medicare or medicaid.

shared_text:
Caroline Bennett‎The Charles School at Ohio Dominican University
August 2 at 12:57 PM ·

🚨NEW PROGRAM ANNOUNCEMENT🚨
MAG is excited to present the LIFT EVERY VOICE INTERNSHIP & CONCERT SERIES in partnership with The Paragon Project & Columbus UMADAOP.
We are looking for a few good INTERNS to complete our inaugural class. Applicants should be in high school or college and have an interest in music, poetry, or dance. The program goal is to give younger performing artists the opportunity to develop their craft, network with artists in and outside of the community, expose you to different platforms, all while enriching the community by creating and providing content that assists in the promotion of healthy, drug and violence-free lifestyle. All workshops are virtual. Interns will receive a weekly stipend for their commitment and participation. SPACE IS LIMITED! See link below to apply:
https://form.jotform.com/maroonartsgroup/MAGInternApp

Are you between the ages of 16-18?

post_text:
Dear Families and Students,
This afternoon, Governor DeWine made the announcement that school buildings will be closed through the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. The Charles School will therefore continue on-line instruction until the end of the academic year. This is heartbreaking news as we miss the students and seeing our community! We plan on providing more details about expectations for learning in the digital platform soon. Please continue to monitor your emails, this Facebook page, and our website for further details. We are still accessible at office@thecharleschool.org and 614-258-8588. We hope you and your family are safe and healthy!
text:

We plan on providing more details about expectations for learning in the digital platform soon. Please continue to monitor your emails, this Facebook page, and our website for further details. We are still accessible at office@thecharleschool.org and 614-258-8588. We hope you and your family are safe and healthy!

post_text:
Check out the Linden LEAP!
The LEAP is free to all passengers 12 years old and up. The two shuttles servicing the route will pick up passengers every 12 minutes. It will take 24 minutes to ride from the first to the last stop. The shuttle operate 7 days a week from 6AM-8PM, except for 9:30AM-10:30AM and 3PM-4:30PM Monday-Friday during school release times per federal mandate. The shuttles can accommodate strollers and wheelchairs and can carry up to 12 passengers.
https://smart.columbus.gov/get-involved/linden-leap
